Component Selectors:
1. Apply kebab-case for component selectors (e.g., app-icon, range-selector)
2. Prefix shared UI components with 'app-' (e.g., app-button, app-dropdown, app-input)
3. Prefix child components by their purpose (e.g., submit-button, location-dropdown, username-input)
4. Prefix feature components with feature name (e.g., dashboard-widget, order-list, chat-details)

Component Files:
1. Name files after the component selector (e.g., app-input.component.html/ts/scss, order-list.component.html/ts/scss)

Utility Files:
1. Prefix by feature or purpose (e.g., date-helper.util.ts, table-pagination.util.ts, order-list.util.ts)

Directive Files:
1. Prefix by feature or purpose -
   currency-mask.directive.ts, alpha-only.directive.ts

State Management Files (NgXs):
1. Prefix files with the entity name -
   order.model.ts, product.action.ts, category.state.ts

Service Files:
1. Prefix by feature or purpose -
   orders.service.ts, http.service.ts, api-config.service.ts

Facade Files:
1. Prefix by domain -
   session.facade.service.ts, order-details.facade.service.ts
